The paper proposes a new approach for improving the performance of Graph Convolutional Networks (GCN) for semi-supervised learning by incorporating higher-order neighborhood information. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Given that the paper focuses on improving the performance of GCN, which is a popular model in the field of machine learning, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. However, the other sub-categories are also relevant to the paper's topic and could be considered as well.
